        <div class="content">
            <div class="card">
                <h2 class="card-title"><i class="fas fa-question-circle"></i> What is OPSEC?</h2>
                <div class="card-content">
                    <p>OPSEC <span class="tooltip">(Operational Security)
                        <span class="tooltiptext">Process of protecting individual pieces of data</span>
                    </span> is a risk management process that encourages organizations to view operations from an adversary's perspective.</p>
                    <p>In the digital world, OPSEC refers to practices that help individuals and organizations protect their data from unauthorized access, tracking, and exploitation.</p>
                    <div class="hacker-text">
                        <p>> INITIATING OPSEC_BASICS.EXE</p>
                        <p>> OPSEC = IDENTIFY CRITICAL INFO + ANALYZE THREATS + APPLY COUNTERMEASURES</p>
                        <p>> PROCESS COMPLETE</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="card">
                <h2 class="card-title"><i class="fas fa-shield-alt"></i> Why Get Into OPSEC?</h2>
                <div class="card-content">
                    <p>In today's interconnected world, your digital footprint is constantly being tracked, analyzed, and often exploited by corporations, governments, and malicious actors.</p>
                    <p>OPSEC helps you:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><span class="pulse"></span>Protect your privacy and personal information</li>
                        <li><span class="pulse"></span>Avoid targeted advertising and manipulation</li>
                        <li><span class="pulse"></span>Prevent identity theft and financial fraud</li>
                        <li><span class="pulse"></span>Secure your communications from surveillance</li>
                        <li><span class="pulse"></span>Maintain control over your personal data</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="card">
                <h2 class="card-title"><i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i> Risks of Ignoring OPSEC</h2>
                <div class="card-content">
                    <p>Failing to practice good OPSEC can lead to:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Complete erosion of personal privacy</li>
                        <li>Data breaches exposing sensitive information</li>
                        <li>Identity theft and financial loss</li>
                        <li>Being targeted by sophisticated phishing attacks</li>
                        <li>Manipulation through personalized propaganda</li>
                        <li>Stalking and harassment facilitated by data brokers</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>Your digital identity becomes a product sold to the highest bidder without your explicit consent.</p>
                    <div class="cyber-button" id="showThreatsBtn">Simulate Data Leak</div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="card">
                <h2 class="card-title"><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Pros of Being OPSEC-Conscious</h2>
                <div class="card-content">
                    <p>Adopting OPSEC practices offers significant benefits:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Greater control over your personal information</li>
                        <li>Reduced risk of identity theft and financial fraud</li>
                        <li>Minimized tracking and personalized manipulation</li>
                        <li>Enhanced security for your devices and communications</li>
                        <li>Peace of mind knowing your data is protected</li>
                        <li>Improved understanding of digital systems and privacy</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="card">
                <h2 class="card-title"><i class="fas fa-graduation-cap"></i> How to Become OPSEC</h2>
                <div class="card-content step-list">
                    <p>Start your OPSEC journey with these steps:</p>
                    <ol>
                        <li><span class="step-number">1</span> Switch to privacy-focused operating systems like Linux</li>
                        <li><span class="step-number">2</span> Avoid products from companies with poor privacy records (like Intel)</li>
                        <li><span class="step-number">3</span> Use reputable VPNs like Mullvad VPN and Windscribe</li>
                        <li><span class="step-number">4</span> Replace Google with privacy-respecting search engines (DuckDuckGo, Startpage)</li>
                        <li><span class="step-number">5</span> Install and use Tor Browser for anonymous browsing</li>
                        <li><span class="step-number">6</span> Use F-Droid instead of Google Play for open-source apps</li>
                        <li><span class="step-number">7</span> Uninstall Meta, Google, and other data-harvesting apps</li>
                        <li><span class="step-number">8</span> Use encrypted messaging apps like Signal</li>
                        <li><span class="step-number">9</span> Regularly audit your online presence and permissions</li>
                        <li><span class="step-number">10</span> Educate yourself continuously about digital privacy</li>
                    </ol>
                    <div class="cyber-button" id="startJourneyBtn">Begin OPSEC Journey</div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="card">
                <h2 class="card-title"><i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> Additional Resources</h2>
                <div class="card-content">
                    <p>Continue your OPSEC education with these resources:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>PrivacyTools.io - Guides and tools for privacy-conscious users</li>
                        <li>The New Oil - Digital security and privacy curriculum</li>
                        <li>Prism Break - Open-source alternatives to proprietary services</li>
                        <li>EFF (Electronic Frontier Foundation) - Digital privacy advocacy</li>
                        <li>r/privacytoolsIO and r/opsec on Reddit</li>
                    </ul>
                    <p>Remember: OPSEC is a continuous process, not a one-time setup.</p>
                    
